net.sf.ehcache.store.compound.impl
Class OverflowToDiskStore

java.lang.Object
  net.sf.ehcache.store.AbstractStore
      net.sf.ehcache.store.compound.CompoundStore
          net.sf.ehcache.store.compound.impl.OverflowToDiskStore
All Implemented Interfaces:
CacheConfigurationListener, Store
public final class OverflowToDiskStore
extends CompoundStore
implements CacheConfigurationListener

Implements an overflow-to-disk store.

When this store's in-memory space becomes full, it pushes Elements off to disk.

Author:
Chris Dennis

bufferFull

public boolean bufferFull()
Some store types, such as the disk stores can fill their write buffers if puts come in too fast. The thread will wait for a short time before checking again.

flush

public void flush()
           throws IOException
Flush elements to persistent store.

This store is not persistent, so this simply clears the in-memory store if clear-on-flush is set for this cache.
